FIFA22 players exploration

FIFA22 players exploration#

You can practice your Python / Pandas / Altair skills on this data file of players from the game FIFA22. The file comes via Kaggle.

import pandas as pd
import altair as alt

I posted the file in our Github repo so that you can access it via a raw link.

Rather than lead you through this, I’ll just leave you with the file. Come up with graphs/analyses you can share.

At first you will probably just be exploring features of the file. It would be nice if you progressed to drawing some conclusions about players / teams / leagues / positions.

import altair as alt

fifa.columns

Index(['sofifa_id', 'player_url', 'short_name', 'long_name',
       'player_positions', 'overall', 'potential', 'value_eur', 'wage_eur',
       'age',
       ...
       'lcb', 'cb', 'rcb', 'rb', 'gk', 'player_face_url', 'club_logo_url',

alt.data_transformers.disable_max_rows()

DataTransformerRegistry.enable('default')

alt.Chart(fifa).mark_circle().encode(x='age',y='wage_eur')

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.scatter(fifa.age,fifa.wage_eur)
plt.grid()
plt.xlabel("Age (years")
plt.ylabel("Wages (euros)")
